TITLE: Trump’s Attack of Powell Tempered by Risk of Market Panic
SUMMARY: President Trump again attacked the chair of the Federal Reserve this week, but advisers say the president has turned more cautious on policies that could stoke extreme financial volatility again.

TITLE: Trump Shifted on Tariffs After Bond Holders Got Jittery. He Held Millions Himself.
SUMMARY: As of August, the president’s investment portfolio showed significantly more in bonds than in stocks. It is unclear if his personal holdings had any bearing on his decisions regarding tariffs.

TITLE: Head of I.R.S. Being Ousted Amid Treasury’s Power Struggle With Elon Musk
SUMMARY: Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent complained to President Trump that the acting commissioner had been installed without his knowledge.

TITLE: Trump’s Trade War With China Puts Bromance With Xi Beyond Reach
SUMMARY: President Trump says he wants Xi Jinping, China’s leader, to call him to talk tariffs. Mr. Xi is ghosting Mr. Trump, and markets are plummeting.

TITLE: Top DOGE Officials Moved From Social Security Administration to Justice Dept.
SUMMARY: The Elon Musk operatives were abruptly shifted to the department’s immigration enforcement unit as part of an expanding effort to use personal data in deportation cases, one official said.

TITLE: Who Is J. Harvie Wilkinson, the Judge Behind a Scathing Rebuke of the White House?
SUMMARY: The judge, a conservative Reagan appointee, wrote a blistering opinion accusing the administration of failing to give a man wrongly deported to El Salvador any semblance of due process.

TITLE: Trump’s Least Favorite Judge Has Friends in High Places
SUMMARY: To President Trump, Judge James E. Boasberg is “a troublemaker” and a “Radical Left Lunatic.” But his record and biography, including a friendship with Justice Brett M. Kavanaugh, say otherwise.

TITLE: A TikTok Influencer Opens Up About Her Skin Picking Condition
SUMMARY: Millions of people compulsively pick their skin or pull their hair. Social media is helping some of them to recover.

TITLE: Under Trump, National Security Guardrails Vanish
SUMMARY: America’s adversaries have more room to operate, at least in the disinformation space, cybersecurity experts say.

TITLE: Rubio Says Trump to ‘Move On’ From Ukraine Peace Talks if No Progress Soon
SUMMARY: “If it is not possible to end the war in Ukraine, we need to move on,” Secretary of State Marco Rubio said as he departed meetings in Paris.

TITLE: With Harvard Threat, Trump Tries to Bend the I.R.S. to His Will
SUMMARY: Since the post-Nixon era, the Internal Revenue Service has had a degree of independence from the White House. President Trump is seeking to change that.

TITLE: Harvard’s Stand Against Trump Is Helping It Raise More Money
SUMMARY: The Trump administration said it would take $2.2 billion in research funds from the school. Some small donors are doing their best to make up for the shortfall.

TITLE: Trump Administration Blames Boasberg for Escalating Tensions Between Courts and White House
SUMMARY: The administration cast the threat by the judge, James E. Boasberg, to open criminal contempt proceedings as another salvo in an increasingly bitter battle between the White House and the courts.

TITLE: Are Easter Baskets Getting Out of Hand?
SUMMARY: Social media feeds are awash in images of lavish baskets overflowing with expensive gifts. Some parents are giving their children bikes. Others are pushing back.

TITLE: The Women Who Think the World Needs More Babies
SUMMARY: At a convention of the pronatalist movement, the relatively few women in attendance agreed: Motherhood needs a rebrand.

TITLE: RFK Jr. Claimed Autism ‘Destroys’ Lives. Autistic People Disagree.
SUMMARY: People in the community called the remarks dehumanizing and warned they could perpetuate harmful stigma.

TITLE: Google Makes History With Rapid-Fire Antitrust Losses
SUMMARY: Within a year, two federal judges declared the tech giant a monopoly in search and ad technology. The tide may be turning for antitrust.

TITLE: Syrians Recount Gas Attack Under Assad as They Seek Justice
SUMMARY: Syria’s ousted dictator, Bashar al-Assad, unleashed a Sarin gas strike on the suburbs of Damascus in 2013, killing at least 1,500. Now, the survivors want justice.

TITLE: U.S. Strikes on Yemeni Port Kill Dozens, Houthis Say
SUMMARY: President Trump has vowed that the Iran-backed Houthi militia will be “completely annihilated.” But forceful American strikes do not seem to have deterred the Yemeni fighters.

TITLE: Milwaukee’s Lead Crisis: Flaky Paint, Closed Schools and a C.D.C. in Retreat
SUMMARY: Some children were exposed to lead and investigators found flaking paint inside aging schools. Two federal experts, expected to help guide the response, have lost their jobs.

TITLE: What We Know About the FSU Shooting
SUMMARY: Two people were killed and six others were injured when a 20-year-old gunman opened fire near the student union building, the police said.

TITLE: If You Care About Your Savings, Pay Attention to Trump’s Attack on The Fed
SUMMARY: The president’s threat to fire Jerome Powell is more than a personal spat. It’s a direct challenge to the economic foundation that has helped America prosper.

TITLE: Christianity in the White House
SUMMARY: President Trump has significantly expanded the power and influence of conservative Christians in government.

TITLE: Wisconsin Supreme Court Says Governor’s 400-Year Edit Was Within Veto Authority
SUMMARY: Gov. Tony Evers, a Democrat, used his veto power to increase school funding limits for four centuries longer than Republican lawmakers in the state had intended.

TITLE: Battling ‘Eat and Flee’ Tourists, Venice Brings Its Entrance Fee Back
SUMMARY: A measure to limit day tourism on peak days began for the second year on Friday, charging day trippers five euros (or 10 for the spontaneous traveler).

TITLE: ‘Psychological Torture’: London Bans Busking in a Famed Tourist Hub
SUMMARY: Noise complaints led the authorities to halt street performances in Leicester Square. Some miss the music. Others found the noise “bloody annoying.”

TITLE: Long-Term Investing Has Gotten Riskier as Trump’s Tariffs Shake the Markets
SUMMARY: President Trump’s policies have shaken the markets. Protect yourself first, and, only then, take advantage of investment bargains, our columnist says.
